<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="F" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Flee" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Flee</orth> (only once, <bibl n="shak. lll 3.66" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL III, 66</bibl>, in the present; in all other passages the impf. or partic. <emph>fled</emph>) 1) to run from danger, and to hasten away in general; a) intr.: <bibl n="shak. ven 793" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 793</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ven 793" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 793</bibl> <bibl n="shak. son 71.3" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 71, 3</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 3.148.3" default="NO" valid="yes">148, 3</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. pp 130" default="NO" valid="yes">Pilgr. 130</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. pp 130" default="NO" valid="yes">Pilgr. 130</bibl> <bibl n="shak. pht 23" default="NO" valid="yes">Phoen. 23</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tgv 5.2.35" default="NO" valid="yes">Gentl. V, 2, 35</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tgv 5.2.35" default="NO" valid="yes">Gentl. V, 2, 35</bibl> <bibl n="shak. tgv 5.3.10" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 3, 10</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wiv 4.5.73" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. IV, 5, 73</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. err 5.154" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. V, 154</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. err 5.154" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. V, 154</bibl> <bibl n="shak. ado 5.1.193" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado V, 1, 193</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ado 5.1.193" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado V, 1, 193</bibl> <bibl n="shak. mnd 3.2.405" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. III, 2, 405</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 5.143.405" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 143</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mv 2.8.16" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. II, 8, 16</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. aww 2.3.305" default="NO" valid="yes">All's II, 3, 305</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 1.2.23" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A I, 2, 23</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 2.2.1" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 2, 1</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 3.2.151" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B III, 2, 151</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 4.8.68" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 8, 68</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 4.10.70" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 10, 70</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 5.5.16" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 V, 5, 16</bibl> <emph>(the soldiers fled</emph> == the soldiers who are fled) etc. etc. With <emph>from</emph>: <cit><quote>the rogue fled from me,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h4 2.4.248" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B II, 4, 248</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. rom 1.1.136" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. I, 1, 136</bibl>. <cit><quote>fled from words,</quote> <bibl n="shak. cor 2.2.76" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. II, 2, 76</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. oth 2.1.152" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. II, 1, 152</bibl>.<lb />b) trans.: <cit><quote>Stafford fled the field,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h4 1.1.18" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B I, 1, 18</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>that which we have fled during the life,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h6 4.7.49" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A IV, 7, 49</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>so fled his enemies my warlike father,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 3h6 2.1.19" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C II, 1, 19</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. mac 5.7.67" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. V, 7, 67</bibl>.
<lb />2) to fly, to be borne through the air with rapidity: <cit><quote>love's golden arrow at him should have fled,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ven 947" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 947</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>I shoot thee at the swain. Thump then and I flee,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lll 3.66" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL III, 66</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>arrows fled not swifter toward their aim,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h4 1.1.123" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B I, 1, 123</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>